$tmp['20_dadpara_English-UTF8'] = "<p>My Roy Family migrated from Kamouraska, Quebec, Canada in the mid 1820s. My 3rd Great Grandfather, Jean Raphael Roy, appears to have been the first Roy to migrate to the Saint John River Valley around 1826.</p><p><span class='blueemphasis'>Jean Raphael Roy</span>, son of Jean Marie Roy and Marie Anne Michaud, married <span class='blueemphasis'>Marie Louis Caron</span>, daughter of Simon Caron and Ursule Belanger on 26 November 1810 at St Louis, Kamouraska, Kamouraska County, Province of Quebec. Their children were also born and baptized at St Louis, Kamouraska, except for Henriette who baptism was registered at St Basile, Madawaska County, New Brunswick, Canada in 1826.</p>";
