$tmp['20_mompara_English-UTF8'] = "My Nadeau Family migrated from Kamouraska, Quebec, Canada in the late 1700s. My 3rd Great Grandfather, Jean Baptiste Nadeau, appears to have been the first Nadeau to migrate to the Saint John River Valley around 1790.<p><span class='blueemphasis'>Jean Baptiste</span>, son of Louis and Marie Genevieve Michaud, married <span class='blueemphasis'>Marie Anne Albert</span>, daughter of Francois Albert and Marie Anne Paradis on 7 August 1788 at Kamouraska, Kamouraska County, Province of Quebec. Their first son, Jean Baptiste's birth and baptism is recorded in the parish registers of St André de Kamouraska on 1 Jul 1794 with a note that he was born on 8 Mar 1794 and that they were living in Madawaska.";
$tmp['20_mompara_French-UTF8'] = "Ma famille Nadeau a émigré de Kamouraska, Québec, Canada vers la fin des 1700s. Mon 3ème grandpère, Jean Baptiste Nadeau, semble avoir été le premier Nadeau à émigrer à la vallée supérieur de la rivière Saint Jean autour de 1790.<p><span class='blueemphasis'>Jean Baptiste</span>, son of Louis and Marie Genevieve Michaud, married <span class='blueemphasis'>Marie Anne Albert</span>, daughter of Francois Albert and Marie Anne Paradis on 7 August 1788 at Kamouraska, Kamouraska County, Province of Quebec. Their first son, Jean Baptiste's birth and baptism is recorded in the parish registers of St André de Kamouraska on 1 Jul 1794 with a note that he was born on 8 Mar 1794 and that they were living in Madawaska.";
